ur. Then call tavily_tool to search \"Mayanoor Karur distance\" or \"Mayanoor village distance from Karur\". Also maybe use tavily to check hotel rates. That's also search category; but we might exceed? The category \"hotel pricing\" maybe also uses search. But we can combine in one search query: \"Hotel Kaveri Residency Karur price\". Could be separate. But rule: \"Do NOT call tools more than once per category\". Category: search? There are two search tools: tavily_tool and serper_tool. Both are search. Probably each counts as same category? Might be considered separate categories: \"hotel pricing\" is a category; we can use one tool call for that. So we can use tavily_tool with query about hotel pricing. That also could include distance info. But we already used tavily for distance. Might need separate calls. Could combine both in one query: \"Mayanoor Karur distance and Hotel Kaveri Residency price\". That might give both. Let's do that.\n\nThus we will call tavily_tool with query: \"Mayanoor distance from Karur and Hotel Kaveri Residency nightly rate\". Then call google_map_tool for Chennai to Karur.\n\nProceed."}}], "created": 1771670463, "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "on_demand", "system_fingerprint": "fp_5a93aea882", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 698, "prompt_tokens": 1876, "total_tokens": 2574, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 651, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": null, "queue_time": 0.195174844, "prompt_time": 0.090858714, "completion_time": 1.5183942419999998, "total_time": 1.609252956}, "usage_breakdown": null, "x_groq": {"id": "req_01khzwkq3gfzhbyrds5hnfnmpr", "seed": 1738548751}}, "prompt_tokens": 1876, "completion_tokens": 698, "agent_id": "Travel_Researcher_bf99fa57-40b5-4a10-b985-8abc3b83752e/bf99fa57-40b5-4a10-b985-8abc3b83752e"}
